caption.text:
Here is how to grow on Instagram in 2024👇

You want to post 70% of your content as reels and 30% as photo content.

If you don’t like or can’t create photo content, then post 100% reels.

70% of your reels should be educational and valuable “how-to” content.
20% should be community-building content.
10% should be promotional and lead generation content.

To make sure that your content actually gets views, you need to take care of two things: first, topics; second, hooks.

First, you want to talk about something that is in demand in your niche. The biggest mistake entrepreneurs and content creators make on Instagram is talking about something they believe their audience is interested in, but when they start doing content research, they realize they are wrong. The topics that are actually in demand in their niche are different.

Second, you want to make sure that your video starts with a catchy hook. You have 3 to 5 seconds to grab people’s attention because attention spans on Instagram today are like a goldfish’s. So, you really need to learn how to create a catchy hook.

Do you want to learn more?

Comment the word LEGIT and I’ll DM you my best 60-minute free course about Instagram growth🔥. 

It’s an in-depth course on how to grow on Instagram with IG reels in 2024-2025. I detail my strategies that helped me reach 4.4 million accounts and gain 30k+ new followers last month.

Comment LEGIT and I’ll DM it to you for free.
